{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/6886", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/6886/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/6886/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/6886/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/6886", "id": 317006524, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MTgzNTc1Mjg0", "number": 6886, "title": "Revert \"Fix performance regression of simple indexing cases (#6793)\"", "user": {"login": "colesbury", "id": 655866, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY1NTg2Ng==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/655866?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury", "html_url": "https://github.com/colesbury", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2018-04-23T22:33:03Z", "updated_at": "2018-04-24T02:22:13Z", "closed_at": "2018-04-24T02:22:13Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/pulls/6886", "html_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/6886", "diff_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/6886.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/6886.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>This reverts commit <a class=\"commit-link\" data-hovercard-type=\"commit\" data-hovercard-url=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/commit/8a016693c0808ec8353370fd4c48f4049a372b74/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/commit/8a016693c0808ec8353370fd4c48f4049a372b74\"><tt>8a01669</tt></a>.</p>\n<p>There are at least two issues with <code>index_select</code>:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>It doesn't handle negative indices</li>\n<li>Duplicate indices cause non-determinism in the backwards</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Repros:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-python\"><pre><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">import</span> torch\n<span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> x <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> torch.randn(<span class=\"pl-c1\">10</span>)\n<span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> x[[<span class=\"pl-k\">-</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>]]</pre></div>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-python\"><pre><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">import</span> torch\n<span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> x <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> torch.randn(<span class=\"pl-c1\">10</span>, <span class=\"pl-v\">device</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">0</span>, <span class=\"pl-v\">requires_grad</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">True</span>)\n<span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> idx <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> torch.ones(<span class=\"pl-c1\">1000000</span>, <span class=\"pl-v\">device</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">0</span>, <span class=\"pl-v\">dtype</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span>torch.int64)\n<span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> grad <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> torch.randn(idx.shape, <span class=\"pl-v\">device</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">0</span>)\n<span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> x[idx].backward(grad)\n<span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">print</span>(x.grad[<span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>])\n<span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> x.grad <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">None</span>\n<span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> x[idx].backward(grad)\n<span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"pl-k\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">print</span>(x.grad[<span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>])</pre></div>\n<p>cc <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=3768583\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/gchanan\">@gchanan</a> <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=9110200\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/fmassa\">@fmassa</a></p>", "body_text": "This reverts commit 8a01669.\nThere are at least two issues with index_select:\n\nIt doesn't handle negative indices\nDuplicate indices cause non-determinism in the backwards\n\nRepros:\n>>> import torch\n>>> x = torch.randn(10)\n>>> x[[-1]]\n>>> import torch\n>>> x = torch.randn(10, device=0, requires_grad=True)\n>>> idx = torch.ones(1000000, device=0, dtype=torch.int64)\n>>> grad = torch.randn(idx.shape, device=0)\n>>> x[idx].backward(grad)\n>>> print(x.grad[1])\n>>> x.grad = None\n>>> x[idx].backward(grad)\n>>> print(x.grad[1])\ncc @gchanan @fmassa", "body": "This reverts commit 8a016693c0808ec8353370fd4c48f4049a372b74.\r\n\r\nThere are at least two issues with `index_select`:\r\n1) It doesn't handle negative indices\r\n2) Duplicate indices cause non-determinism in the backwards\r\n\r\nRepros:\r\n```python\r\n>>> import torch\r\n>>> x = torch.randn(10)\r\n>>> x[[-1]]\r\n```\r\n\r\n```python\r\n>>> import torch\r\n>>> x = torch.randn(10, device=0, requires_grad=True)\r\n>>> idx = torch.ones(1000000, device=0, dtype=torch.int64)\r\n>>> grad = torch.randn(idx.shape, device=0)\r\n>>> x[idx].backward(grad)\r\n>>> print(x.grad[1])\r\n>>> x.grad = None\r\n>>> x[idx].backward(grad)\r\n>>> print(x.grad[1])\r\n```\r\n\r\ncc @gchanan @fmassa "}